Similar to the inner product argument, the verification in weighted inner product argument too can be expressed as a single equation by unrolling recursion.</p>

<p><span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mtable width="100%"><mtr><mtd width="50%"></mtd><mtd><mrow><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">g</mtext><mrow><mi>e</mi><mo>⋅</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>⋅</mo><mtext mathvariant="bold">s</mtext></mrow></msup><mo>⋅</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">h</mtext><mrow><mi>e</mi><mo>⋅</mo><msup><mi>s</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>⋅</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">s</mtext><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow></msup><mo>⋅</mo><msup><mi>g</mi><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><mo>⊙</mo><msup><mi>s</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></mrow></msup><mo>⋅</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><msup><mi>δ</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup></msup><mo><mover><mo><mo>=</mo></mo><mo stretchy="false" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">?</mo></mover></mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mover accent="true"><mi>A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msup><mo>⋅</mo><mrow><mo fence="true">(</mo><munderover><mo>∏</mo><mrow><mi>j</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msub><mtext>log</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>m</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></munderover><msubsup><mi>L</mi><mi>j</mi><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⋅</mo><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mi>j</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mrow></msubsup><mo>⋅</mo><msubsup><mi>R</mi><mi>j</mi><mrow><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⋅</mo><msubsup><mi>x</mi><mi>j</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></msubsup><mo fence="true">)</mo></mrow><mo>⋅</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mi>A</mi><mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em">′</mo></msup><msup><mo stretchy="fal